Durban - A 34-year-old woman was killed when two cars crashed on the N3 in Camperdown in KwaZulu-Natal on Thursday morning. Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson said ER24 as well as other services found the two cars in the middle of the road. Meiring said a woman was trapped inside one of the cars and assessments showed that she had sustained numerous injuries and was in a critical condition. “Rescue services had to use specialized equipment to free the woman from the vehicle, an operation lasting one hour. Once freed, paramedics treated the woman and provided her with advanced life support interventions,” said Meiring. He said the woman was treated on the scene before being transported to Mediclinic Pietermaritzburg. However, during transportation, the woman needed CPR and advanced life support were initiated to revive her. A short time after she was handed over to hospital staff, she succumbed to her injuries, said Meiring. The cause of the crash is unknown but police were on scene and are investigating. Daily News